      <h2>About the Author</h2>
      <div class="author-bio">
        <p>Dawn Clark is a passionate science fiction author with a lifelong love for books that began with the Trixie Belden series. As a devoted sci-fi fan, she's fascinated by the potential of space exploration and its endless possibilities, weaving intricate stories set against the vast cosmic backdrop.</p>
        <p>The writing process for "The Chronicles of the Few" has been a whirlwind of emotions. At times, ideas poured out like lightning, and Dawn could barely keep up with the torrent of inspiration. Other times, the words trickled slowly, and she counted the sand grains on the beach, waiting for inspiration to strike.</p>
        <p>When she's not writing, you can find Dawn curled up with a good book (intriguing mysteries are her weakness!) or chasing after Bentley, her mischievous Jack Russell. Sometimes, she finds solace in stargazing. There's something truly awe-inspiring about gazing at the cosmos, a feeling she tries to capture in her stories.</p>
        <p>I'm truly grateful to anyone who purchases my book and leaves a review. Each review will inspire me to evolve my writing in a way that resonates more with my readers and my fans. I'm excited to embark on this journey and grow as an author, fueled by the support and enthusiasm of my audience. Dive deeper into the world of 'The Chronicles of the Few' <a href="link-to-book-page">here</a>. Sign up for my newsletter to stay up-to-date on my latest projects and writing adventures! <a href="link-to-signup-form">here</a></p>
        <p>I'm already brainstorming ideas for my next sci-fi adventure, and I can't wait to share them with you!</p>
        <p>Dawn is happily married and blessed with a grown child and an adorable grandson. She finds joy in the simple things, like playing fetch with Bentley and witnessing his infectious enthusiasm for life.</p>
